verbose_text: The C. elegans DAF-16 / Foxo transcription factor can promote resistance to diverse stresses including starvation, heat shock, proteotoxicity, oxygen radicals, pathogenic bacteria, and high metal concentrations, and even promotes germline apoptosis in a manner that can repress germ cell tumors.
